3. Formal Pantheon statement

Any two representations are intertranslatable to the extent that they preserve a shared semantic invariant under transformation.

That should probably be stored as a canonical invariant.

Because that is the law behind:
	•	JSON ↔ YAML
	•	schema ↔ code
	•	prose ↔ spec
	•	diagram ↔ text
	•	notes ↔ action plan
	•	doctrine ↔ implementation

