4. File types as skins, not essence

This is the key shift.

Most systems treat file types as primary.
Pantheon treats them as skins over structure.

So:
	•	JSON and YAML are two skins over hierarchical data
	•	CSV and SQL tables are two skins over tabular relations
	•	Markdown and HTML are two skins over document structure
	•	prose and formal schema are two skins over semantic content
	•	code and diagrams are two skins over process logic

This is exactly what your Pattern Prime and Rehydration Doctrine was already moving toward.

This is the operationalization.

