5. Pantheon Intermediate Representation

To make this rigorous, Pantheon should define a canonical intermediate layer.

Call it something like:

ThoughtObject / Canonical Meaning Object (CMO)

A CMO stores:

id: string
artifact_type: string
entities: []
relations: []
constraints: []
sequence: []
metadata: {}
semantic_invariant: string
loss_tolerance: low | medium | high
rehydration_targets: []

This is the thing every representation maps into and out of.

So the transformation is no longer:

JSON → YAML

It becomes:

JSON → CMO → YAML

And later:

meeting transcript → CMO → project plan
diagram → CMO → API schema
prose doctrine → CMO → governance rules

That is much stronger.

