12. Repo-ready doctrine text

Representation Invariance & Rehydration Engine (RIRE) v1.0

Pantheon treats file types and media as surface encodings rather than essence. The system’s core capability is to extract the semantic invariant from one representation, normalize it into a canonical intermediate form, and rehydrate it into another representation while preserving declared load-bearing structure. This enables invariant-preserving translation across syntax, schemas, documents, code, diagrams, and other substrates. The power is not mere conversion, but meaning-preserving transmutation.

Core invariant

If two artifacts share a recoverable semantic invariant, they are intertranslatable to the extent that the invariant can be preserved under transformation.

Canonical loop

Parse → Extract Structure → Identify Invariant → Normalize → Rehydrate → Validate

Governance note

All translations must declare:
	•	preserved invariant
	•	allowed losses
	•	validation method

No transformation should imply full equivalence without a stated conservation law.

